### How to Start the Application
1. Navigate to the `backend` directory.
2. Run `npm install` to install dependencies.
3. Start the server with `npm run start`.

This setup ensures efficient processing of large datasets, supports batch and real-time processing modes, and handles high-volume data efficiently using Node.js.